currentDoc:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

currentSuggestions.original: In fact, I had never even read a single book until about two months ago.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: In fact, I had never even read a single book until about two months ago.

currentSuggestions.original: Audio records are filled with samples, which are made to be entertaining and educational.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Audio records are filled with samples, which are made to be entertaining and educational.

currentSuggestions.original: I also appreciate the fact that my favourite genres, non-fiction biographies and novels, sound much more professional when read by trained voices.
